{"title":"Thinking Across Scales","markdown":{"yaml":{"format":{"html":{"css":"assets/css/custom.css","page-layout":"full","toc":false,"title-block-banner":false}}},"headingText":"Thinking Across Scales","containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n\n::::: hero-shell\n::: {.hero-image role=\"img\" aria-label=\"Placeholder for Everglades photograph\"}\n![logo](assets/images/branding/logo.png){.hero-image-photo}\n:::\n\n::: {.hero-copy .container}\n\nHow studying landscapes became a way of understanding the world.\n:::\n:::::\n\n:::: {.section .intro-shell .container}\n::: {.intro-copy .text-center .mx-auto}\nI was trained as a landscape ecologist, where the most important lesson was not about landscapes themselves, but about learning to think across scales. Over time, that perspective expanded beyond ecology into computation, organizations, design, and everyday life. This website is an evolving record of that journey.\n:::\n::::\n\n:::::::::: {.section .container-fluid .feature-cards-shell}\n::::::::: {.row .gx-4 .gy-4}\n::::: {.col-12 .col-md-6 .col-xl-3}\n:::: feature-card\n::: feature-icon\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-scaling-icon lucide-scaling\"><path d=\"M12 3H5a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v14a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h14a2 2 0 0 0 2-2v-7\"/><path d=\"M14 15H9v-5\"/><path d=\"M16 3h5v5\"/><path d=\"M21 3 9 15\"/></svg>\n:::\n\n### Atlas\n\nWalking through landscapes\n\n[Explore →](journeys/)\n::::\n:::::\n\n::::: {.col-12 .col-md-6 .col-xl-3}\n:::: feature-card\n::: feature-icon\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-brain-circuit-icon lucide-brain-circuit\"><path d=\"M12 5a3 3 0 1 0-5.997.125 4 4 0 0 0-2.526 5.77 4 4 0 0 0 .556